File Handling
____ ________

File handling is an object that gives more options like creating , updating, and two
ways to open a file...

1. open()

syntax:

do =open('file_name','mode')
----
-----
---
close()

eg:

do = open('shankarbio.txt','r')
print(do.read())


2. with(keyword)

syntax:

with open('file_name','mode') as do:

with open('shankarbio.txt','r') as do:
    print(do.read())

Modes
_____

r--> used to read the file, incase if the file doesnt exist it will raise error.

eg:
with open('shankarbio.txt','r') as do:
    print(do.read())

w--> used to write the text inside the file and it will overide the text inside file.
     Incase if the file is not present it will create a new file with name given.
eg:

with open('shankarbio.txt','w') as do:
    print(do.write('he is bosedk'))

with open('shankardk.txt','w') as do:
    print(do.write('he is bosedk'))
    
a--> this is used to add the text at last position inside the file .

eg:

with open('shankardk.txt','a') as do:
    print(do.write('he is jaffa'))

x--> used to create a new by adding inside the file, incase if the file is present
     it will raise an error ..
     
eg:
with open('shankardk.txt','x') as do:
    print(do.write('he is jaffa'))


write()
_______

--> the function is used to add the text inside a file or update a file with new text.

eg:
with open('shankarbio.txt','w') as do:
    print(do.write('he is bosedk'))

with open('shankardk.txt','a') as do:
    print(do.write('he is jaffa'))


read()
______

--> this function is used to read the file and this read() will read file chunk by chunk..
     we can also specify the size .
     
eg:
with open('shankarbio.txt','r') as do:
    print(do.read())

with open('shankarbio.txt','r') as do:
    print(do.read(10))


readline()
__________

--> this readline() function will read only one line at a time..

eg:
with open('shankarbio.txt','r') as do:
    print(do.readline())

readlines()
___________

--> this function will read whole file and give it in a list each line in one index in that list.

eg:

with open('shankarbio.txt','r') as do:
    print(do.readlines())

